==English==
===Etymology===

From {{Gr.}} [[δεκα]] (deca) ten.

===Prefix===
[[Category:English prefixes]]
'''deca-''' ''or'' '''deka-'''

#[[ten]].
#:''decagon''
#In the [[International System of Units]] and other [[metric]] systems of units, multiplying the [[unit]] to which it is attached by 10. Symbol: da
#*'''Usage notes:  This prefix is not used in official scientific contexts.  For example, "1 dam" (one decametre or dekametre) is written instead as either "10 m" or "0.01 km".'''

